snippet: After a third national championship in four years, Alabama Coach Nick Saban was already getting antsy about next season, and impatient with questions about the N.F.L.
abstract: Alabama head football coach Nick Saban, who has collected four national championships, including three he has won with Alabama in past four seasons, is already getting antsy about next season, and impatient with questions about the NFL.

byline.contributor: Tim Rohan contributed reporting from Fort Lauderdale, Fla.

lead_paragraph: After a third national championship in four years, Alabama Coach Nick Saban was already getting antsy about next season, and impatient with questions about the N.F.L.

headline.seo: The Saban Way: Already Moving On
headline.main: The Saban Way: That Was Nice, Now Move On
headline.print_headline: The Saban Way: That Was Nice, Now Move On
